A slain Russian lawmaker was honored Tuesday as a martyr to democratic ideals in a stately funeral service in which anger mingled freely with tears.
Afterward, Galina Starovoitova was to be buried alongside some of Russia's greatest national heroes.
The stirring tribute to Starovoitova, a feisty liberal whose killing remains a mystery, was indicative of the depth of national feeling over her death.
``To stop us, they want to scare us.
They will never succeed,'' former Deputy Prime Minister Anatoly Chubais said at the funeral for Starovoitova.
``We will fulfill the goals she sacrificed her life for''.
